<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer10612046870387024923">Mark D. Campbell is a native of Houston, Texas. He studied at the University of Houston before finally entering a career path in the federal criminal justice system in late 2005. He is the author of the Amazon bestselling H7N9 series (Top 50 in Medical Fiction Oct 2019, Nov 2019, Dec 2019, Jan 2020). Currently, his chosen genres include works heavily related to the post-apocalyptic horror and dyst</span>
  <span id="freeText10612046870387024923" style="display:none">Mark D. Campbell is a native of Houston, Texas. He studied at the University of Houston before finally entering a career path in the federal criminal justice system in late 2005. He is the author of the Amazon bestselling H7N9 series (Top 50 in Medical Fiction Oct 2019, Nov 2019, Dec 2019, Jan 2020). Currently, his chosen genres include works heavily related to the post-apocalyptic horror and dystopian science fiction fields. When he isn't busy killing large swaths of the world's population, he indulges in travel and is a purveyor of books. Some of his favorite authors include of Robert McCammon, Richard Matheson, and, of course, Stephen King.<br /><br />Mark welcomes e-mails and can be reached at authormarkcampbell@outlook.com.<br /><br />Tweet him or follow him at @mdmark23dc</span>
  <a data-text-id="10612046870387024923" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
